  <summary date="2017-09-12T04:00:00Z" status="Introduced in House">Medicare Buy-In and Health Care Stabilization Act of 2017

This bill makes a series of changes relating to health insurance options and costs. Among other things, the bill establishes a Medicare buy-in option for individuals aged 50 to 64, requires the Centers for Medicare &amp; Medicaid Services to negotiate drug prices for Medicare beneficiaries, and establishes an individual market reinsurance fund.</summary>
